(:summary    "Coding system from \"use utf8\" in perl code"
 :created    "2009"
 :updated    "2010"
 :license    "GPL-3"
 :authors    (("Kevin Ryde" . "user42@zip.com.au"))
 :maintainer ("Kevin Ryde" . "user42@zip.com.au")
 :provided   (perl-use-utf8-coding)
 :required   ((("emacs-core" advice)))
 :homepage   "http://user42.tuxfamily.org/perl-use-utf8-coding"
 :commentary "\
This spot of code gets an Emacs coding system from a \"use utf8;\" pragma
in Perl code.  That pragma means strings and identifiers have or may have
utf-8 encoded wide chars.  See the `perl-use-utf8-auto-coding-function'
docstring below for more.")
